revision.text:
Usually you cannot manipulate the player using [[ACS]] because they do not have a [[TID]], as a TID of zero is invalid. You can assign a TID to the player using the following script.

 Script 1 {{SType|Enter}}
 {
 	[[Thing_ChangeTID]](0, 1000 + [[PlayerNumber]]()); // This assigns the TID
 }

This changes the TID of the activator (which is automatically the player because of the nature of {{SType|Enter}} scripts) to 1000 plus the player number, which will give each player a separate TID (i.e player 1 is 1000, player 2 is 1001 etc).

